1
00:00:36,110 --> 00:00:41,240
♪In rain or shine♪

2
00:00:41,780 --> 00:00:46,870
♪When you're around,
the sun shines through♪

3
00:00:47,220 --> 00:00:52,640
♪Spare ourselves the endless thoughts
and guessing games♪

4
00:00:52,930 --> 00:00:58,880
♪Let's just meet
and escape these frames♪

5
00:00:59,360 --> 00:01:02,600
♪I stand within the shadows deep♪

6
00:01:02,880 --> 00:01:08,030
♪My hand outstretched,
your rescue I keep♪

7
00:01:08,220 --> 00:01:12,850
♪Even if the world falls apart♪

8
00:01:13,170 --> 00:01:15,870
♪No distance is too far♪

9
00:01:17,260 --> 00:01:21,390
♪To stop us from coming together♪

10
00:01:21,720 --> 00:01:27,710
♪Through the night,
you're at the end of the line♪

11
00:01:28,710 --> 00:01:32,730
♪To protect you is my humble wish♪

12
00:01:32,920 --> 00:01:36,920
♪Farewell, to the timid soul I knew♪

13
00:01:37,270 --> 00:01:42,550
♪It was you who made me brave and new♪

14
00:01:42,550 --> 00:01:46,180
=Always Home=
(Adapted from Xiao Ge's novel, Always Home)

15
00:01:46,260 --> 00:01:49,180
=Episode 13=
(Time, Time, Please Slow Down)

16
00:01:50,140 --> 00:01:52,270
The best mom.

17
00:01:53,500 --> 00:01:56,500
I love you.

18
00:01:58,270 --> 00:01:58,990
I'll use this one.

19
00:01:59,470 --> 00:02:01,390
Mom, aren't you on the night shift?

20
00:02:01,390 --> 00:02:02,750
Why are you back so early?

21
00:02:02,990 --> 00:02:04,860
Are you sure it's your mom?

22
00:02:05,470 --> 00:02:06,140
Dad!

23
00:02:06,580 --> 00:02:07,190
Dad!

24
00:02:08,400 --> 00:02:09,620
Weren't you not coming back?

25
00:02:09,620 --> 00:02:10,900
Why did you suddenly come back?

26
00:02:10,950 --> 00:02:11,990
It's your mom's birthday.

27
00:02:11,990 --> 00:02:13,890
I wanted to surprise her.
How could I not come?

28
00:02:14,070 --> 00:02:15,020
Dad! Listen.

29
00:02:15,420 --> 00:02:17,300
I've got everything ready.

30
00:02:17,670 --> 00:02:18,460
That's great!

31
00:02:18,720 --> 00:02:19,580
Hurry, give it to me!

32
00:02:19,580 --> 00:02:20,650
Let me wash my hands first.

33
00:02:20,790 --> 00:02:21,550
You have no idea

34
00:02:23,620 --> 00:02:24,460
how hard it is

35
00:02:24,700 --> 00:02:26,350
for me to take a leave.

36
00:02:27,700 --> 00:02:28,460
What happened, Dad?

37
00:02:29,020 --> 00:02:29,670
Huan'er.

38
00:02:30,670 --> 00:02:31,300
Uh...

39
00:02:31,700 --> 00:02:33,790
Why are my mouth-rinsing cup,
toothbrush, and towel

40
00:02:33,860 --> 00:02:34,860
gone from the washroom?

41
00:02:34,920 --> 00:02:35,880
Where did they go?

42
00:02:36,040 --> 00:02:37,860
Mom said it was too occupied there,

43
00:02:37,990 --> 00:02:38,990
so she put them away.

44
00:02:39,070 --> 00:02:40,070
Let me call and ask her.

45
00:02:40,070 --> 00:02:40,860
Don't!

46
00:02:41,070 --> 00:02:41,740
Don't call her.

47
00:02:41,740 --> 00:02:43,540
If you call her,
the surprise will be ruined.

48
00:02:43,550 --> 00:02:44,390
Yeah, you're right!

49
00:02:45,180 --> 00:02:47,020
You see, I hardly come home,

50
00:02:47,230 --> 00:02:49,120
and now I feel like
this isn't even my house.

51
00:02:49,950 --> 00:02:50,420
Dad,

52
00:02:50,790 --> 00:02:52,110
I'll go and buy you a new set.

53
00:02:52,140 --> 00:02:52,670
Don't!

54
00:02:52,670 --> 00:02:53,510
It's just downstairs.

55
00:02:53,510 --> 00:02:54,110
Forget it.

56
00:02:54,230 --> 00:02:55,560
It's late now. It's not safe.

57
00:02:55,820 --> 00:02:57,140
I come up with a solution.

58
00:02:57,280 --> 00:02:58,020
What is it?

59
00:02:58,960 --> 00:03:00,830
I'll just rub
my hands together, that'll do.

60
00:03:00,990 --> 00:03:02,510
Dad, don't be

61
00:03:02,580 --> 00:03:03,550
disgusting.

62
00:03:03,620 --> 00:03:04,670
Your mom is so unreasonable

63
00:03:04,740 --> 00:03:05,950
to put all my stuff away.

64
00:03:13,110 --> 00:03:14,390
Luckily, this was not discovered.

65
00:03:28,020 --> 00:03:28,830
Oh my god.

66
00:03:29,670 --> 00:03:31,790
Huan'er, is there any milk left?

67
00:03:31,830 --> 00:03:33,230
This milk expired days ago.

68
00:03:34,020 --> 00:03:35,510
Dad, try to search for it again.

69
00:03:35,900 --> 00:03:37,350
Doesn't your mom cook for you?

70
00:03:37,840 --> 00:03:38,950
I've just found five or six

71
00:03:38,950 --> 00:03:40,180
bottles of expired stuff here.

72
00:03:41,420 --> 00:03:42,350
And also, this spatula

73
00:03:42,400 --> 00:03:44,260
is not even cleaned properly
after being used.

74
00:03:44,830 --> 00:03:45,860
Is your mom normally

75
00:03:45,860 --> 00:03:46,840
abusing you at home?

76
00:03:47,740 --> 00:03:49,580
How am I abusing her?

77
00:03:50,700 --> 00:03:52,020
Get lost!

78
00:03:52,240 --> 00:03:53,110
You mean I abuse her?

79
00:03:53,110 --> 00:03:54,640
If you're not at ease,
take her away!

80
00:03:54,660 --> 00:03:56,020
Look, this is expired.

81
00:03:56,020 --> 00:03:57,420
I'm playing both mom and dad roles.

82
00:03:57,420 --> 00:03:58,230
It's not easy for me.

83
00:03:58,230 --> 00:03:59,510
Do you think it's easy for me?

84
00:03:59,990 --> 00:04:01,510
Please come back to the topic.

85
00:04:01,510 --> 00:04:02,390
This milk is expired.

86
00:04:02,390 --> 00:04:04,300
So what? I'll use it as fertilizer
for the plants!

87
00:04:04,300 --> 00:04:05,700
I didn't give it to her to drink!

88
00:04:05,700 --> 00:04:07,270
Are you just arguing for the sake of it?

89
00:04:07,270 --> 00:04:09,070
You disappeared all year round.

90
00:04:09,070 --> 00:04:10,540
And you have
the nerve to lecture me?

91
00:04:10,560 --> 00:04:12,040
What do you mean? Why am I never home?

92
00:04:12,100 --> 00:04:13,830
I work hard all year.

93
00:04:13,860 --> 00:04:15,830
I raise the kid and take care of her.

94
00:04:15,860 --> 00:04:17,500
I live like a widow. It's easy for me?

95
00:04:17,500 --> 00:04:18,500
You've gone overboard.

96
00:04:18,500 --> 00:04:19,670
A widow? Then, who am I here?

97
00:04:19,670 --> 00:04:20,550
I'm just like a widow.

98
00:04:20,550 --> 00:04:21,740
Am I out there making money?

99
00:04:21,740 --> 00:04:22,860
Making money? Give it to me.

100
00:04:22,860 --> 00:04:24,680
- I gave you all the money!
- That little bit?

101
00:04:24,700 --> 00:04:26,710
I gave you money and
you bought such a thing?

102
00:04:26,710 --> 00:04:28,820
- What can't I buy this?
- This could poison someone.

103
00:04:28,820 --> 00:04:29,910
What's wrong with you?

104
00:04:29,940 --> 00:04:31,470
You keep buying expired stuff.

105
00:04:31,480 --> 00:04:33,140
How was I supposed
to know it was expired?

106
00:04:33,220 --> 00:04:34,740
I don't want to argue with you anymore.

107
00:04:34,740 --> 00:04:36,060
I just got off my night shift.

108
00:04:36,060 --> 00:04:37,820
I'll sleep first,
then only battle with you.

109
00:04:37,820 --> 00:04:39,300
Stay or leave, it's up to you.

110
00:04:50,110 --> 00:04:51,260
You scared me!

111
00:04:51,990 --> 00:04:53,670
Morning. You wake up so early.

112
00:04:55,180 --> 00:04:55,590
Morning.

113
00:04:59,550 --> 00:05:01,060
Why are you up so early?

114
00:05:02,740 --> 00:05:03,620
What else?

115
00:05:04,060 --> 00:05:05,180
Taking out the rubbish.

116
00:05:06,030 --> 00:05:06,590
Oh yeah.

117
00:05:06,740 --> 00:05:08,080
You have to take out the rubbish.

118
00:05:11,400 --> 00:05:12,740
It's still early in the morning.

119
00:05:12,800 --> 00:05:13,940
Why are you in your pajamas

120
00:05:14,560 --> 00:05:16,140
and standing in front of my house?

121
00:05:16,820 --> 00:05:17,350
I...

122
00:05:19,910 --> 00:05:21,550
I woke up early too.

123
00:05:22,060 --> 00:05:22,590
Go on.

124
00:05:22,910 --> 00:05:23,790
Keep making things up.

125
00:05:24,460 --> 00:05:25,380
Hold on, Chen Huan'er.

126
00:05:25,380 --> 00:05:26,470
Your look right now...

127
00:05:26,480 --> 00:05:28,160
You really see me
as just a brother, huh?

128
00:05:29,030 --> 00:05:29,470
I...

129
00:05:31,260 --> 00:05:32,820
I just...

130
00:05:35,230 --> 00:05:36,590
Wanted to ask you for tutoring.

131
00:05:41,710 --> 00:05:42,260
You...

132
00:05:43,500 --> 00:05:44,230
Want me

133
00:05:45,470 --> 00:05:46,420
to tutor you?

134
00:05:47,680 --> 00:05:49,380
You're talking nonsense
in the morning.

135
00:05:49,380 --> 00:05:50,470
Are you sleepwalking?

136
00:05:50,470 --> 00:05:50,860
Are you...

137
00:05:50,860 --> 00:05:51,230
Ouch!

138
00:05:51,260 --> 00:05:51,820
It's painful.

139
00:05:57,150 --> 00:05:58,550
My parents are quarreling.

140
00:05:59,820 --> 00:06:01,590
I want to stay away
from it at your place.

141
00:06:02,910 --> 00:06:03,790
Is that okay?

142
00:06:22,990 --> 00:06:23,380
(Song.)

143
00:06:23,400 --> 00:06:24,180
(Come to my house!)

144
00:06:24,180 --> 00:06:25,200
(Chen Huan'er needs you.)

145
00:06:55,740 --> 00:06:56,260
Wait,

146
00:06:57,110 --> 00:06:58,350
should I change

147
00:06:58,350 --> 00:07:00,060
my outfits too?

148
00:07:00,380 --> 00:07:01,470
Otherwise, I look completely

149
00:07:01,520 --> 00:07:02,560
out of place with you two.

150
00:07:05,150 --> 00:07:05,990
Are you okay?

151
00:07:07,740 --> 00:07:09,500
I'm fine now.

152
00:07:11,790 --> 00:07:12,420
What's so funny?

153
00:07:13,550 --> 00:07:14,420
Nothing, go on.

154
00:07:15,990 --> 00:07:16,790
Sorry

155
00:07:17,670 --> 00:07:19,380
for waking you both up so early.

156
00:07:21,350 --> 00:07:23,150
I just don't understand

157
00:07:23,740 --> 00:07:24,350
why my parents

158
00:07:24,350 --> 00:07:25,360
suddenly started fighting.

159
00:07:25,590 --> 00:07:26,790
They used to argue,

160
00:07:26,790 --> 00:07:28,110
but never this bad.

161
00:07:28,710 --> 00:07:29,790
Why are they fighting?

162
00:07:30,230 --> 00:07:30,940
I don't know.

163
00:07:31,710 --> 00:07:33,180
When I woke up and started washing up,

164
00:07:33,240 --> 00:07:34,400
my dad was making breakfast

165
00:07:34,400 --> 00:07:36,040
and my mom returned
from her night shift.

166
00:07:36,040 --> 00:07:37,560
Then, suddenly they started fighting.

167
00:07:38,670 --> 00:07:39,470
It feels like

168
00:07:40,260 --> 00:07:41,420
they argue because of me.

169
00:07:41,550 --> 00:07:42,820
Didn't you ask them

170
00:07:42,990 --> 00:07:43,590
why

171
00:07:43,590 --> 00:07:44,740
they were fighting?

172
00:07:44,860 --> 00:07:46,180
How am I supposed to ask?

173
00:07:47,990 --> 00:07:48,550
Yeah.

174
00:07:50,940 --> 00:07:51,910
What about your parents?

175
00:07:52,620 --> 00:07:54,110
What do they usually fight about?

176
00:07:54,500 --> 00:07:55,230
My parents?

177
00:07:57,030 --> 00:07:58,670
My parents...

178
00:07:59,150 --> 00:08:00,790
Anything from international wars

179
00:08:01,260 --> 00:08:02,940
to the most trivial things.

180
00:08:03,470 --> 00:08:05,670
As long as they breathe the same air,

181
00:08:05,720 --> 00:08:07,060
they'll find a reason to argue.

182
00:08:07,350 --> 00:08:08,940
But usually, within a minute,

183
00:08:09,030 --> 00:08:10,860
my dad will find some way

184
00:08:10,860 --> 00:08:11,470
to coax my mom.

185
00:08:11,990 --> 00:08:13,620
And soon after he calms her down,

186
00:08:13,620 --> 00:08:14,500
within another minute,

187
00:08:14,500 --> 00:08:15,700
they'll start fighting again.

188
00:08:15,840 --> 00:08:17,260
Sometimes, it gets really dramatic.

189
00:08:18,160 --> 00:08:19,920
There's never a fight
happened at my house.

190
00:08:21,470 --> 00:08:22,860
Never?

191
00:08:23,550 --> 00:08:24,230
Never.

192
00:08:25,500 --> 00:08:27,060
Every day, it's just my dad

193
00:08:27,350 --> 00:08:28,180
who gets scolded.

194
00:08:32,660 --> 00:08:34,710
Now when you guys mention it,

195
00:08:35,000 --> 00:08:36,760
I think my family
isn't so bad after all.

196
00:08:38,070 --> 00:08:39,430
But seriously, it's weird.

197
00:08:39,860 --> 00:08:40,470
See,

198
00:08:40,950 --> 00:08:41,430
since

199
00:08:41,470 --> 00:08:43,140
they look down on each other so much,

200
00:08:43,140 --> 00:08:45,540
why did they choose to be together
when they were young?

201
00:08:45,780 --> 00:08:47,500
Haven't you heard the saying?

202
00:08:47,710 --> 00:08:48,660
Many people say

203
00:08:48,710 --> 00:08:50,190
that before having kids,

204
00:08:50,260 --> 00:08:51,590
parents have a good relationship.

205
00:08:52,740 --> 00:08:53,900
Who told you this nonsense?

206
00:08:54,020 --> 00:08:55,260
So, according to you,

207
00:08:55,260 --> 00:08:56,900
why did our parents have us?

208
00:08:57,190 --> 00:08:57,780
To suffer?

209
00:08:58,710 --> 00:08:59,500
Who knows?

210
00:09:00,350 --> 00:09:01,470
All beings endure suffering.

211
00:09:15,710 --> 00:09:16,190
Oh, right.

212
00:09:16,710 --> 00:09:17,860
Let me show you two

213
00:09:17,860 --> 00:09:19,590
something I found last night.

214
00:09:26,220 --> 00:09:27,470
- Where is it?
- What is it?

215
00:09:29,950 --> 00:09:30,710
This and this.

216
00:09:34,780 --> 00:09:35,380
Do you get it?

217
00:09:36,860 --> 00:09:37,540
So basically,

218
00:09:37,780 --> 00:09:38,380
your dad

219
00:09:39,380 --> 00:09:40,990
and your mom are actually fine.

220
00:09:49,230 --> 00:09:50,260
Wait, does that mean...

221
00:09:56,140 --> 00:09:56,990
Your dad

222
00:09:58,190 --> 00:09:59,070
and your mom?

223
00:10:00,430 --> 00:10:01,860
Are you crazy?

224
00:10:01,990 --> 00:10:02,780
My mom?

225
00:10:03,500 --> 00:10:04,260
My mom?

226
00:10:06,070 --> 00:10:06,780
My mom?

227
00:10:07,350 --> 00:10:09,070
How could that possibly be my mom?

228
00:10:15,380 --> 00:10:15,860
Alright.

229
00:10:16,140 --> 00:10:17,260
Move a little this way.

230
00:10:17,500 --> 00:10:17,860
This way?

231
00:10:17,860 --> 00:10:18,260
Yeah.

232
00:10:18,310 --> 00:10:18,620
This.

233
00:10:18,700 --> 00:10:19,350
This background.

234
00:10:19,350 --> 00:10:19,830
Yes.

235
00:10:20,260 --> 00:10:20,740
Alright.

236
00:10:21,380 --> 00:10:22,260
One, two.

237
00:10:24,540 --> 00:10:25,430
No more film.

238
00:10:25,860 --> 00:10:26,590
Sorry about that.

239
00:10:26,590 --> 00:10:27,990
Let me check if I have a spare roll.

240
00:10:28,230 --> 00:10:28,780
Hold on.

241
00:10:29,230 --> 00:10:29,740
No rush.

242
00:10:29,830 --> 00:10:30,430
Take your time.

243
00:10:33,780 --> 00:10:34,380
Yifan,

244
00:10:36,230 --> 00:10:38,830
why do I feel that he has

245
00:10:39,950 --> 00:10:40,780
other intentions

246
00:10:41,110 --> 00:10:42,710
towards you?

247
00:10:57,900 --> 00:10:58,740
Xichi.

248
00:10:59,660 --> 00:11:00,500
Good morning, Mom.

249
00:11:01,350 --> 00:11:02,190
Morning, Aunt Lin.

250
00:11:02,220 --> 00:11:02,940
Morning, Aunt Lin.

251
00:11:03,900 --> 00:11:04,590
You three

252
00:11:05,020 --> 00:11:06,780
slept in this room last night?

253
00:11:09,590 --> 00:11:10,780
Mom, what are you thinking?

254
00:11:10,780 --> 00:11:11,740
How could it be possible

255
00:11:11,740 --> 00:11:12,960
to fit three of us on my bed?

256
00:11:13,000 --> 00:11:13,900
They just got here.

257
00:11:16,620 --> 00:11:17,260
Just got here?

258
00:11:17,320 --> 00:11:19,190
Then, you probably haven't
had breakfast yet.

259
00:11:19,200 --> 00:11:20,160
What do you want to eat?

260
00:11:20,180 --> 00:11:20,990
I'll make it for you.

261
00:11:23,070 --> 00:11:23,500
Mom.

262
00:11:23,950 --> 00:11:24,590
What's wrong?

263
00:11:24,940 --> 00:11:26,020
Can I ask you a question?

264
00:11:27,260 --> 00:11:28,020
Did Uncle Song

265
00:11:29,260 --> 00:11:30,660
like you

266
00:11:31,020 --> 00:11:32,230
when

267
00:11:33,590 --> 00:11:34,260
he was young?

268
00:11:35,500 --> 00:11:36,190
What?

269
00:11:48,830 --> 00:11:50,140
You're back for B and C again?

270
00:11:51,070 --> 00:11:52,540
What a special style you have!

271
00:11:53,230 --> 00:11:54,020
Why are you here?

272
00:11:54,900 --> 00:11:56,620
Delivering photos to Jing Xichi.

273
00:11:57,190 --> 00:11:58,310
I have something for you.

274
00:11:58,590 --> 00:12:00,230
Regarding the last math problem,

275
00:12:00,430 --> 00:12:01,310
I thought about it.

276
00:12:02,140 --> 00:12:03,950
I think that not everything

277
00:12:03,950 --> 00:12:04,860
needs an answer.

278
00:12:05,110 --> 00:12:05,990
What if the answer

279
00:12:06,020 --> 00:12:06,860
isn't what you want?

280
00:12:08,310 --> 00:12:09,430
Study it carefully.

281
00:12:09,860 --> 00:12:11,140
This is all I can do to help.

282
00:12:14,310 --> 00:12:15,140
Jing Xichi.

283
00:12:15,350 --> 00:12:16,070
I'm here.

284
00:12:16,140 --> 00:12:16,860
Open the door.

285
00:12:19,625 --> 00:12:21,334
(Sense and Sensibility)

286
00:12:42,620 --> 00:12:43,260
Dad,

287
00:12:44,020 --> 00:12:45,900
Mom doesn't like surprises the most.

288
00:12:45,950 --> 00:12:46,830
If you do this,

